      <lg type="edition">
<l>viḻukkaṭip paṟainta muḻukuraṉ muraca</l>
<l>‍<supplied>moḻukkuṭai ma</supplied>ruṅki ṉorumoḻit tāka</l>
<l>varaveṟi yurumi ṉuraṟupu cilaippa</l>
<l>vorutā mākiya perumai yōrun</l>
<l>tampukaḻ niṟīic ceṉṟumāyn taṉarē</l>
<l>yataṉā laṟavōṉ makaṉē ma<supplied>ṟavōr cemmāl</supplied></l>
<l><gap quantity="26" reason="lost" unit="character"/>uraippak <supplied>kēṇmati</supplied></l>
<l>niṉṉūṟṟam piṟaraṟiyātu</l>
<l>piṟarkūṟiya moḻiteriyā</l>
<l>ñāyiṟ ṟellai yāḷviṉaik kutavi</l>
<l>yiravi ṉellai varuvatu nāṭi</l>
<l>yurai<gap quantity="41" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l>uḻavoḻi perumpaka ṭaḻitiṉ ṟāṅkuc</l>
<l>ceṅkaṇ makaḷiroṭu ciṟutuṉi yaḷaii</l>
<l>yaṅkaṭ ṭēṟa lāykalat tukuppak</l>
<l>keṭalarun tiruva<gap quantity="29" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l>maṭaivēṇṭunark kiṭaiyarukā</l>
<l>taviḻvēṇṭunark kiṭaiyaruḷi</l>
<l>viṭaivīḻttuc cūṭukiḻippa</l>
<l>nīrnilai perutta vārmaṇa laṭaikaraik</l>
<l>kāvutoṟum<gap quantity="26" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l>maṭaṅka luṇmai māyamō vaṉṟē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While whole-voiced drums beaten by excellent sticks (1)</l>
<l>being of one word on the side of conduct(?) (2) </l>
<l>resounded, roaring like snake-attacking thunder, (3)</l>
<l>even great people who had become unique, (4)</l>
<l>having established their fame, went [and] vanished. (5)</l>
<l>Therefore, son of a righteous man, eminence among the brave, (6)</l>
<l>listen when talk………….. (7)</l>
<l>bein unknown to others with respect to your strength, (8)</l>
<l>not understanding the words spoken by others, (9)</l>
<l>contributing to manly work within the boundaries of day, (10)</l>
<l>examining what comes within the boundaries of night, (11)</l>
<l>word………………………………. (12)</l>
<l>mingling in little disgust with red-eyed women, (14)</l>
<l>like a big bull that ceased ploughing eats straw, (13)</l>
<l>while they(?) pour fine toddy from choice vessels, (15)</l>
<l>fortune difficult to lose……………………. (16)</l>
<l>not stinting among those who want gifts, (17)</l>
<l>being gracious among those who want rice, (18)</l>
<l>while they(?) thrown down a ram [and] tear the roast, (19) </l>
<l>on the settled shore with overflowing sand where the position of the water rose, (20)</l>
<l>in every grove……………. (21)</l>
<l>is the existence of Death and illusion? It is not. (22)</l>
</lg>
